Realizing I am spending most of my time navigating around this depression. Far too much time thinking and worrying than I am doing. I am doing but it’s sort of a panic mode, just scouring and firing off applications. Having crazy negative thoughts about every possible thing. I have been here before, I have climbed my way out of it. I know how to do this. I just need a new approach. Talked to Garret, there are a few things on the horizon. A job with those guys would be the most opportune thing. Eric Morris recommended a restaurant job. Need to follow up on it. Have to hit the ground running tomorrow. Start doing stuff differently.
